#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/_index.md:0
msgid "Learning to create your first applications using Kirigami\n"
msgstr "Naučte sa vytvoriť svoje prvé aplikácie pomocou Kirigami\n"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/_index.md:30
msgid ""
"This tutorial will guide you through the process of creating your own "
"convergent application using the [Kirigami framework](/frameworks/kirigami). "
"A *convergent application*, in this context, means people can use the "
"program easily regardless of the device it is running on. If it is on a "
"desktop computer, it will adapt to a large screen and a mouse and keyboard; "
"if it is being used on a mobile device, it will accept input from a "
"touchscreen and adapt to a smaller portrait screen. And so on."
msgstr ""
"Tento tutoriál vás prevedie procesom vytvárania vašej vlastnej konvergentnej "
"aplikácie pomocou [frameworku Kirigami](/frameworks/kirigami). *Konvergentná "
"aplikácia* v tomto kontexte znamená, že ľudia môžu program jednoducho "
"používať bez ohľadu na zariadenie, na ktorom beží. Ak je na stolnom "
"počítači, prispôsobí sa veľkej obrazovke a myši s klávesnicou; ak sa používa "
"na mobilnom zariadení, prijme vstup z dotykovej obrazovky a prispôsobí sa "
"menšej obrazovke na výšku. A tak ďalej."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/_index.md:38
msgid ""
"Kirigami is built on top of the QML language and Qt Quick Controls 2 "
"components provided by the Qt project. QML has built in support for touch "
"systems, which makes it ideal for mobile apps. Qt Quick components are "
"reusable visual items we can use when building our applications' interfaces. "
"Kirigami is a set of Qt Quick components designed for creating convergent "
"applications."
msgstr ""
"Kirigami je postavené na jazyku QML a komponentoch Qt Quick Controls 2 "
"poskytovaných projektom Qt. QML má zabudovanú podporu pre dotykové systémy, "
"čo ho robí ideálnym pre mobilné aplikácie. Komponenty Qt Quick sú "
"znovupoužiteľné vizuálne prvky, ktoré môžeme použiť pri zostavovaní rozhraní "
"našich aplikácií. Kirigami je sada komponentov Qt Quick navrhnutých na "
"vytváranie konvergentných aplikácií."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/_index.md:44
msgid ""
"While you will use QML to create the visual part of your application, the "
"business logic—the code that does the heavy lifting for your application's "
"functionality—should be written in a different language. We will also "
"explore how to integrate our business logic with our UI in the tutorials "
"below."
msgstr ""
"Zatiaľ čo QML budete používať na vytvorenie vizuálnej časti vašej aplikácie, "
"obchodná logika—kód, ktorý zabezpečuje hlavnú funkcionalitu vašej aplikácie—"
"by mala byť napísaná v inom jazyku. V tutoriáloch nižšie tiež preskúmame, "
"ako integrovať našu obchodnú logiku s naším používateľským rozhraním."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/_index.md:49
msgid ""
"First, you will need to set up a new project in a language of your choice. "
"The introduction will show you how to make a small, but functional Kirigami "
"application."
msgstr ""
"Najskôr budete musieť nastaviť nový projekt v jazyku podľa vášho výberu. "
"Úvod vám ukáže, ako vytvoriť malú, ale funkčnú aplikáciu Kirigami."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/_index.md:51
msgid ""
"You will be shown the basics of how to deal with colors and text in your "
"application, and you will get acquainted with most QML components. Next, you "
"will get acquainted with most of the QML components you might want to use "
"and how they look like. This section won't touch any business logic at all, "
"only QML code."
msgstr ""
"Ukážeme vám základy práce s farbami a textom vo vašej aplikácii a oboznámite "
"sa s väčšinou komponentov QML. Ďalej sa oboznámite s väčšinou komponentov "
"QML, ktoré by ste mohli chcieť použiť a ako vyzerajú. Táto sekcia sa "
"nedotkne žiadnej obchodnej logiky, iba kódu QML."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/_index.md:53
msgid ""
"You will get a deep dive into more advanced topics that concern manipulating "
"the data that will be shown in your program."
msgstr ""
"Hlboko sa ponoríte do pokročilejších tém týkajúcich sa manipulácie s dátami "
"zobrazovanými vo vašom programe."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/_index.md:55
msgid ""
"Lastly, you will be presented with Kirigami Addons, a series of quality-of-"
"life components that you can use to, among other things, design the Settings "
"of your application."
msgstr ""
"Nakoniec vám budú predstavené Kirigami Addons, séria komponentov zvyšujúcich "
"kvalitu, ktoré môžete použiť okrem iného na návrh nastavení vašej aplikácie."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-about/index.md:0
msgid "FormCard About pages"
msgstr "Stránky FormCard O aplikácii"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-about/index.md:0
msgid "Learn to create About pages to credit your application."
msgstr ""
"Naučte sa vytvárať stránky O aplikácii na uvedenie autorov vašej aplikácie."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-about/index.md:8
#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:8
#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:8
msgid ""
"Kirigami Addons is an additional set of visual components that work well on "
"mobile and desktop and are guaranteed to be cross-platform. It uses Kirigami "
"under the hood to create its components."
msgstr ""
"Kirigami Addons je dodatočná sada vizuálnych komponentov, ktoré dobre "
"fungujú na mobiloch aj desktopoch a je zaručená ich multiplatformovosť. Na "
"vytváranie svojich komponentov používa Kirigami pod kapotou."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-about/index.md:10
msgid ""
"Some of those components allow you to credit your work and the work of other "
"contributors in your project, as well as mention the frameworks being used "
"in your application: [AboutKDE](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-"
"kirigamiaddons-formcard-aboutkdepage.html) and [AboutPage](https://api.kde."
"org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-aboutpage.html)."
msgstr ""
"Niektoré z týchto komponentov vám umožňujú uviesť vašu prácu a prácu ďalších "
"prispievateľov vo vašom projekte, ako aj spomenúť frameworky používané vo "
"vašej aplikácii: [AboutKDE](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-"
"formcard-aboutkdepage.html) a [AboutPage](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-"
"kirigamiaddons-formcard-aboutpage.html)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-about/index.md:12
msgid "About KDE"
msgstr "O KDE"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-about/index.md:14
msgid ""
"Each new button we created in the previous step should open a new page. You "
"can add new pages by instantiating them as [Components](docs:qtqml;QtQml."
"Component) and then using `pageStack.layers.push()` for each button to load "
"that page in our `Main.qml`:"
msgstr ""
"Každé nové tlačidlo, ktoré sme vytvorili v predchádzajúcom kroku, by malo "
"otvoriť novú stránku. Nové stránky môžete pridať ich inštanciovaním ako "
"[Components](docs:qtqml;QtQml.Component) a potom použitím `pageStack.layers."
"push()` pre každé tlačidlo na načítanie tej stránky v našom `Main.qml`:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-about/index.md:18
msgid ""
"That's it really! All it takes is instantiating `FormCard.AboutKDE`. You "
"should see something like this after clicking the [AboutKDE](https://api.kde."
"org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-aboutkdepage.html) button:"
msgstr ""
"To je naozaj všetko! Stačí inštanciovať `FormCard.AboutKDE`. Po kliknutí na "
"tlačidlo [AboutKDE](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"aboutkdepage.html) by ste mali vidieť niečo takéto:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-about/index.md:22
msgid "About Page"
msgstr "Stránka O aplikácii"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-about/index.md:24
msgid ""
"The application's [AboutPage](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-"
"formcard-aboutpage.html) is slightly more complex, but it's still very "
"simple to use."
msgstr ""
"[AboutPage](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"aboutpage.html) aplikácie je o niečo zložitejšia, ale stále je veľmi "
"jednoduchá na použitie."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-about/index.md:26
msgid ""
"For a simple about page that uses the data set in by `KAboutData::"
"setApplicationData(aboutData);` in `main.cpp` add the following to your "
"`Main.qml`:"
msgstr ""
"Pre jednoduchú stránku O aplikácii, ktorá používa dáta nastavené cez "
"`KAboutData::setApplicationData(aboutData);` v `main.cpp`, pridajte do vášho "
"`Main.qml` nasledovné:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-about/index.md:30
msgid "The About page of our application should look like this:"
msgstr "Stránka O aplikácii našej aplikácie by mala vyzerať takto:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-about/index.md:34
msgid "Using JSON instead of KAboutData"
msgstr "Použitie JSON namiesto KAboutData"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-about/index.md:36
msgid ""
"Instead of letting your about page get information from [KAboutData](docs:"
"kcoreaddons;KAboutData), it is possible to pass a JSON object directly. You "
"will still need to use [QApplication::setWindowIcon()](docs:qtgui;"
"QGuiApplication::setWindowIcon) in your `main.cpp` in order for your "
"application icon to show up."
msgstr ""
"Namiesto toho, aby vaša stránka O aplikácii získavala informácie z "
"[KAboutData](docs:kcoreaddons;KAboutData), je možné odovzdať objekt JSON "
"priamo. Stále budete musieť použiť [QApplication::setWindowIcon()](docs:"
"qtgui;QGuiApplication::setWindowIcon) vo vašom `main.cpp`, aby sa zobrazila "
"ikona vašej aplikácie."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-about/index.md:38
msgid "Create a `MyAboutPage.qml` like this:"
msgstr "Vytvorte `MyAboutPage.qml` takto:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-about/index.md:42
msgid "And then adjust your `Main.qml` to include your new about page:"
msgstr ""
"A potom upravte váš `Main.qml` tak, aby zahŕňal vašu novú stránku O "
"aplikácii:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-about/index.md:46
msgid ""
"The main JSON object here contains the keys `displayName`, `productName`, "
"`homepage` and so on. The keys `authors`, `credits`, `translators` and "
"`licenses` can each be passed an array of objects. The objects passed to "
"`authors`, `credits` and `translators` share the same keys so that they can "
"be displayed each in their own section, while `licenses` includes the keys "
"`name`, `text` and `spdx` for each license added, as it is not uncommon for "
"the same project to include multiple licenses."
msgstr ""
"Hlavný objekt JSON tu obsahuje kľúče `displayName`, `productName`, "
"`homepage` a tak ďalej. Kľúčom `authors`, `credits`, `translators` a "
"`licenses` je možné odovzdať pole objektov. Objekty odovzdané do `authors`, "
"`credits` a `translators` zdieľajú rovnaké kľúče, takže každý sa môže "
"zobraziť vo vlastnej sekcii, zatiaľ čo `licenses` obsahuje kľúče `name`, "
"`text` a `spdx` pre každú pridanú licenciu, pretože nie je neobvyklé, že "
"rovnaký projekt obsahuje viacero licencií."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-about/index.md:48
msgid ""
"These keys are optional, but a reasonable minimum amount of keys is expected "
"to make your application have no empty fields: `displayName`, `version`, "
"`description`, `homepage`, `copyrightStatement` and `authors`. You are "
"encouraged to fill as many key as possible, however."
msgstr ""
"Tieto kľúče sú voliteľné, ale očakáva sa rozumný minimálny počet kľúčov, aby "
"vaša aplikácia nemala prázdne polia: `displayName`, `version`, "
"`description`, `homepage`, `copyrightStatement` a `authors`. Odporúča sa "
"však vyplniť čo najviac kľúčov."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:0
msgid "Form delegates in your settings pages"
msgstr "Delegáty formulárov na vašich stránkach nastavení"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:0
msgid "Create elegant custom settings pages."
msgstr "Vytvorte elegantné vlastné stránky nastavení."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:10
msgid ""
"You have learned how to add [About and AboutKDE pages](/docs/getting-started/"
"kirigami/addons-about) to your application. Now you will be able to use "
"their same inner components to create your settings pages."
msgstr ""
"Naučili ste sa pridať [stránky O aplikácii a O KDE](/docs/getting-started/"
"kirigami/addons-about) do vašej aplikácie. Teraz budete môcť použiť rovnaké "
"vnútorné komponenty na vytvorenie vašich stránok nastavení."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:12
msgid "The project structure should look like this:"
msgstr "Štruktúra projektu by mala vyzerať takto:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:23
msgid "Needed Changes"
msgstr "Potrebné zmeny"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:25
msgid "Change `Main.qml` to include our new Settings page:"
msgstr "Zmeňte `Main.qml` tak, aby zahŕňal našu novú stránku Nastavení:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:85
msgid ""
"We can now start checking out the components used to create our Settings "
"page: the Form Card and its Delegates."
msgstr ""
"Teraz môžeme začať skúmať komponenty používané na vytvorenie našej stránky "
"Nastavení: Form Card a jeho delegáty."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:87
msgid "Form Delegates"
msgstr "Delegát"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:89
msgid "FormCard and FormCardPage"
msgstr "FormCard a FormCardPage"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:91
msgid ""
"[FormCard.FormCard](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formcard.html) is the main component we will be using to group all its child "
"components, the Delegates."
msgstr ""
"[FormCard.FormCard](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formcard.html) je hlavný komponent, ktorý budeme používať na zoskupenie "
"všetkých jeho podriadených komponentov, delegátov."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:93
msgid ""
"We used a form card in the [Kirigami Addons introduction](/docs/getting-"
"started/kirigami/addons-introduction) before. Its main purpose is to serve "
"as a container for other components while following a color different from "
"the background, in a similar manner to a [Kirigami.Card](docs:kirigami;org."
"kde.kirigami.Card)."
msgstr ""
"Formulárovú kartu sme už použili v [úvode do Kirigami Addons](/docs/getting-"
"started/kirigami/addons-introduction). Jej hlavným účelom je slúžiť ako "
"kontajner pre ďalšie komponenty s farbou odlišnou od pozadia, podobne ako "
"[Kirigami.Card](docs:kirigami;org.kde.kirigami.Card)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:95
msgid "Create a new `SettingsPage.qml` file:"
msgstr "Vytvorte nový súbor `SettingsPage.qml`:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:103
#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:107
msgid "This is where all our delegates go!"
msgstr "Tu budú všetky naše delegáty!"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:112
msgid ""
"Since we are making a separate QML file for our Settings page, and since we "
"need to prepare for potential scrolling in our page, we use a [FormCard."
"FormCardPage](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formcardpage.html), which inherits [Kirigami.ScrollablePage](docs:kirigami;"
"org.kde.kirigami.ScrollablePage)."
msgstr ""
"Keďže vytvárame samostatný súbor QML pre našu stránku Nastavení a keďže sa "
"musíme pripraviť na prípadné posúvanie na našej stránke, používame [FormCard."
"FormCardPage](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formcardpage.html), ktorý dedí z [Kirigami.ScrollablePage](docs:kirigami;org."
"kde.kirigami.ScrollablePage)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:114
msgid ""
"The nice thing about the form card page is that it comes with an internal "
"layout, so no additional ColumnLayout is needed and our delegates can be "
"added directly to it."
msgstr ""
"Pekná vec na stránke formulárovej karty je, že prichádza s vnútorným "
"rozložením, takže nie je potrebný žiadny ďalší ColumnLayout a naše delegáty "
"je možné pridať priamo do nej."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:116
msgid ""
"{{< alert color=\"info\" title=\"Note\" >}} It is possible to use FormCard "
"delegates directly with a Kirigami.ScrollablePage, but in that case you will "
"need to add your own layouts. {{< /alert >}}"
msgstr ""
"{{< alert color=\"info\" title=\"Poznámka\" >}} Je možné použiť delegáty "
"FormCard priamo s Kirigami.ScrollablePage, ale v tom prípade budete musieť "
"pridať vlastné rozloženia. {{< /alert >}}"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:120
msgid "FormHeader"
msgstr "Hlavička"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:122
msgid ""
"For every [FormCard](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formcard.html) you want to create, you can create a [FormHeader](https://api."
"kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formheader.html) just before it. "
"The header uses bold text and shows up right above the form card."
msgstr ""
"Pre každý [FormCard](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formcard.html), ktorý chcete vytvoriť, môžete vytvoriť [FormHeader](https://"
"api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formheader.html) tesne pred "
"ním. Hlavička používa tučný text a zobrazuje sa priamo nad formulárovou "
"kartou."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:133
#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:141
msgid "Our delegates go here..."
msgstr "Tu budú naše delegáty..."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:146
msgid "FormTextDelegate and FormSectionText"
msgstr "FormTextDelegate a FormSectionText"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:148
msgid "Let's start simple, with plain text."
msgstr "Začnime jednoducho, s obyčajným textom."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:150
msgid ""
"[FormSectionText](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formsectiontext.html) simply adds a thin delegate containing a label. "
"[FormTextDelegate](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formtextdelegate.html) has text and a grayed out description."
msgstr ""
"[FormSectionText](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formsectiontext.html) jednoducho pridá tenký delegát obsahujúci štítok. "
"[FormTextDelegate](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formtextdelegate.html) má text a zošednutý popis."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:186
msgid ""
"We add some dummy text for the hypothetical theme detection. If we wanted to "
"have actual color scheme detection, in the future it could be done similarly "
"to [Neochat](https://apps.kde.org/neochat) ([code here](https://invent.kde."
"org/network/neochat/-/blob/master/src/settings/colorschemer.cpp)), making "
"use of a C++ model with [KColorSchemeManager](https://api.kde.org/"
"kcolorschememanager.html)."
msgstr ""
"Pridáme zástupný text pre hypotetickú detekciu témy. Keby sme chceli "
"skutočnú detekciu farebnej schémy, v budúcnosti by to bolo možné urobiť "
"podobne ako v [Neochat](https://apps.kde.org/neochat) ([kód tu](https://"
"invent.kde.org/network/neochat/-/blob/master/src/settings/colorschemer."
"cpp)), využitím C++ modelu s [KColorSchemeManager](https://api.kde.org/"
"kcolorschememanager.html)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:188
msgid ""
"In the Online Accounts section, we see an additional property, [leading]"
"(https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formtextdelegate."
"html#leading-prop). We can add an [Item](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qml-qtquick-"
"item.html) to it so that it appears before the text. Its opposite property, "
"[trailing](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formtextdelegate.html#trailing-prop), would be able to show an Item after "
"the text, but we won't use it in our program."
msgstr ""
"V sekcii Online účty vidíme dodatočnú vlastnosť [leading](https://api.kde."
"org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formtextdelegate.html#leading-prop). "
"Môžeme do nej pridať [Item](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qml-qtquick-item.html), "
"aby sa zobrazil pred textom. Opačná vlastnosť [trailing](https://api.kde.org/"
"qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formtextdelegate.html#trailing-prop) by "
"mohla zobraziť Item za textom, ale v našom programe ju nepoužijeme."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:190
msgid ""
"We use a [Kirigami.Icon](docs:kirigami;org.kde.kirigami.primitives.Icon) "
"here for simplicity, but this could also be implemented using a Kirigami "
"Addons [Avatar](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-components-"
"avatar.html) that grabs the information from a model, [as is done in Neochat]"
"(https://invent.kde.org/network/neochat/-/blob/master/src/settings/"
"AccountsPage.qml)."
msgstr ""
"Pre jednoduchosť tu používame [Kirigami.Icon](docs:kirigami;org.kde.kirigami."
"primitives.Icon), ale toto by sa dalo implementovať aj pomocou [Avatara]"
"(https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-components-avatar.html) "
"Kirigami Addons, ktorý získava informácie z modelu, [ako sa to robí v "
"Neochat](https://invent.kde.org/network/neochat/-/blob/master/src/settings/"
"AccountsPage.qml)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:192
msgid "It should end up looking like this:"
msgstr "Výsledok by mal vyzerať takto:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:196
msgid "FormButtonDelegate"
msgstr "Delegát"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:198
msgid ""
"The [FormButtonDelegate](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-"
"formcard-formbuttondelegate.html) is visually similar to a FormTextDelegate, "
"but it is clickable and shows an arrow pointing to the right. We used it in "
"the [Kirigami Addons introduction](/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-"
"introduction) before."
msgstr ""
"[FormButtonDelegate](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formbuttondelegate.html) je vizuálne podobný FormTextDelegate, ale je "
"klikateľný a zobrazuje šípku smerujúcu doprava. Použili sme ho predtým v "
"[úvode do Kirigami Addons](/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-"
"introduction)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:200
msgid ""
"While the FormTextDelegate had the [leading](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-"
"kirigamiaddons-formcard-formtextdelegate.html#leading-prop) and [trailing]"
"(https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formtextdelegate."
"html#trailing-prop) properties to show an item before and after the main "
"content, the FormButtonDelegate only has the [leading](https://api.kde.org/"
"qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formbuttondelegate.html#leading-prop) "
"property, because the right side is occupied by the arrow."
msgstr ""
"Zatiaľ čo FormTextDelegate mal vlastnosti [leading](https://api.kde.org/qml-"
"org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formtextdelegate.html#leading-prop) a "
"[trailing](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formtextdelegate.html#trailing-prop) na zobrazenie položky pred a za hlavným "
"obsahom, FormButtonDelegate má iba vlastnosť [leading](https://api.kde.org/"
"qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formbuttondelegate.html#leading-prop), "
"pretože pravá strana je obsadená šípkou."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:241
msgid ""
"We use its [icon.name](https://doc.qt.io/Qt-6/qml-qtquick-controls-"
"abstractbutton.html#icon.name-prop) property to set a plus (+) icon to "
"appear after the space where the [leading](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-"
"kirigamiaddons-formcard-formbuttondelegate.html#leading-prop) would appear, "
"and before the main content. This is a common pattern to indicate your "
"button will add something to a list."
msgstr ""
"Používame jeho vlastnosť [icon.name](https://doc.qt.io/Qt-6/qml-qtquick-"
"controls-abstractbutton.html#icon.name-prop) na nastavenie ikony plus (+), "
"aby sa zobrazila za miestom, kde by sa objavil [leading](https://api.kde.org/"
"qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formbuttondelegate.html#leading-prop), a "
"pred hlavným obsahom. Toto je bežný vzor na označenie, že vaše tlačidlo "
"pridá niečo do zoznamu."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:243
msgid ""
"Since this example is for simple illustrative purposes, we don't delve deep "
"into what would be done once the button is clicked: it just prints \"Clicked!"
"\" to the terminal. We _could_ make a new page for account creation that "
"adds another user to a model, then push the page into view, similarly to "
"what we did in `Main.qml`."
msgstr ""
"Keďže tento príklad je na jednoduché ilustračné účely, neponárame sa hlboko "
"do toho, čo by sa stalo po kliknutí na tlačidlo: jednoducho vypíše \"Clicked!"
"\" do terminálu. _Mohli by sme_ vytvoriť novú stránku na vytvorenie účtu, "
"ktorá pridá ďalšieho používateľa do modelu, a potom stránku zobraziť, "
"podobne ako sme to urobili v `Main.qml`."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:247
msgid "FormRadioDelegate, FormCheckDelegate and FormSwitchDelegate"
msgstr "FormRadioDelegate, FormCheckDelegate a FormSwitchDelegate"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:249
msgid ""
"The RadioButton, CheckBox and Switch are very commonly used components in "
"any user interface. Kirigami Addons provides them as [FormRadioDelegate]"
"(https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formradiodelegate."
"html), [FormCheckDelegate](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-"
"formcard-formcheckdelegate.html) and [FormSwitchDelegate](https://api.kde."
"org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formswitchdelegate.html)."
msgstr ""
"RadioButton, CheckBox a Switch sú veľmi bežne používané komponenty v každom "
"používateľskom rozhraní. Kirigami Addons ich poskytuje ako "
"[FormRadioDelegate](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formradiodelegate.html), [FormCheckDelegate](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-"
"kirigamiaddons-formcard-formcheckdelegate.html) a [FormSwitchDelegate]"
"(https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formswitchdelegate."
"html)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:251
msgid ""
"Their only main properties are `text` and `description`. They are different "
"in usage because they all inherit [AbstractButton](docs:qtquickcontrols;"
"QtQuick.Controls.AbstractButton), and so you are expected to use its signals "
"and handlers: checked and onChecked, toggled and onToggled, clicked and "
"onClicked."
msgstr ""
"Ich jediné hlavné vlastnosti sú `text` a `description`. Líšia sa v "
"používaní, pretože všetky dedia z [AbstractButton](docs:qtquickcontrols;"
"QtQuick.Controls.AbstractButton), a preto sa očakáva, že budete používať "
"jeho signály a obsluhy: checked a onChecked, toggled a onToggled, clicked a "
"onClicked."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:253
msgid ""
"We want to create some autosave functionality in our application, and we "
"want to only show its settings if the user has enabled this functionality. "
"Create a new section using a [FormCard](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-"
"kirigamiaddons-formcard-formcard.html) and a [FormHeader](https://api.kde."
"org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formheader.html), then add a "
"[FormSwitchDelegate](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formswitchdelegate.html) and a [FormRadioDelegate](https://api.kde.org/qml-"
"org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formradiodelegate.html)."
msgstr ""
"Chceme vytvoriť funkciu automatického ukladania v našej aplikácii a chceme "
"zobraziť jej nastavenia iba v prípade, že používateľ túto funkciu povolil. "
"Vytvorte novú sekciu pomocou [FormCard](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-"
"kirigamiaddons-formcard-formcard.html) a [FormHeader](https://api.kde.org/"
"qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formheader.html), potom pridajte "
"[FormSwitchDelegate](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formswitchdelegate.html) a [FormRadioDelegate](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-"
"kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formradiodelegate.html)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:280
msgid ""
"We bind the visibility of each radio button to a switch, so they only appear "
"when the switch is enabled."
msgstr ""
"Viažeme viditeľnosť každého prepínacieho tlačidla na prepínač, takže sa "
"objavia iba keď je prepínač zapnutý."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:282
msgid "Best Practices"
msgstr "Osvedčené postupy"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:284
msgid "<details><summary>Click here to read more</summary>\n"
msgstr "<details><summary>Click here to read more</summary>\n"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:286
msgid ""
"If you have some programming background in imperative languages such as C++, "
"you might be tempted to set the [checked](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qml-qtquick-"
"controls-abstractbutton.html#checked-prop) property of the switch to turn "
"the visibility of the radio buttons to `true` with a JavaScript assignment "
"such as:"
msgstr ""
"Ak máte nejaké programátorské skúsenosti s imperatívnymi jazykmi ako C++, "
"mohli by ste byť v pokušení nastaviť vlastnosť [checked](https://doc.qt.io/"
"qt-6/qml-qtquick-controls-abstractbutton.html#checked-prop) prepínača na "
"zapnutie viditeľnosti prepínacích tlačidiel na `true` pomocou priradenia v "
"JavaScripte ako napríklad:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:296
msgid ""
"This is not very efficient for QML's declarative language and its signals "
"and slots. Try to use QML bindings like in the case of `visible: autosave."
"checked` as much as possible instead of JavaScript expressions."
msgstr ""
"Toto nie je veľmi efektívne pre deklaratívny jazyk QML a jeho signály a "
"sloty. Pokúste sa používať väzby QML ako v prípade `visible: autosave."
"checked` čo najviac namiesto výrazov JavaScripte."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:298
msgid ""
"See [this page](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qtquick-bestpractices.html#prefer-"
"declarative-bindings-over-imperative-assignments) for details."
msgstr ""
"Podrobnosti nájdete na [tejto stránke](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qtquick-"
"bestpractices.html#prefer-declarative-bindings-over-imperative-assignments)."

