#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:306
msgid ""
"To test our checkbox, we can add a new [FormCheckDelegate](https://api.kde."
"org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formcheckdelegate.html) to our "
"General section."
msgstr ""
"Na otestovanie nášho zaškrtávacieho políčka môžeme pridať nový "
"[FormCheckDelegate](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formcheckdelegate.html) do našej sekcie Všeobecné."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:331
msgid ""
"Here we use the [signal handler](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qtqml-syntax-signals."
"html) called [onToggled](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qml-qtquick-controls-"
"abstractbutton.html#toggled-signal) to show some dummy text to simulate a "
"tray icon appearing in the system. If you really wanted to, you could easily "
"implement a tray icon using KDE's [KStatusNotifierItem](https://api.kde.org/"
"kstatusnotifieritem-index.html) or Qt's [SystemTrayIcon](https://doc.qt.io/"
"qt-6/qml-qt-labs-platform-systemtrayicon.html)."
msgstr ""
"Tu používame [obsluhu signálu](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qtqml-syntax-signals."
"html) s názvom [onToggled](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qml-qtquick-controls-"
"abstractbutton.html#toggled-signal) na zobrazenie ukážkového textu "
"simulujúceho zobrazenie ikony v systémovej lište. Ak by ste naozaj chceli, "
"mohli by ste jednoducho implementovať ikonu v systémovej lište pomocou "
"[KStatusNotifierItem](https://api.kde.org/kstatusnotifieritem-index.html) od "
"KDE alebo [SystemTrayIcon](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qml-qt-labs-platform-"
"systemtrayicon.html) od Qt."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:333
msgid "So far our application should look like this:"
msgstr "Naša aplikácia by zatiaľ mala vyzerať takto:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:337
msgid "FormComboBoxDelegate"
msgstr "FormComboBoxDelegate"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:339
msgid ""
"The common ComboBox component can be created using a [FormComboBoxDelegate]"
"(https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formcomboboxdelegate.html)."
msgstr ""
"Bežný komponent ComboBox možno vytvoriť pomocou [FormComboBoxDelegate]"
"(https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formcomboboxdelegate.html)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:341
msgid ""
"This combobox has several useful properties we can make use of: [editable]"
"(https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formcomboboxdelegate.html#editable-prop), [displayText](https://api.kde.org/"
"qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formcomboboxdelegate.html#displayText-"
"prop) and [displayMode](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-"
"formcard-formcomboboxdelegate.html#displayMode-prop)."
msgstr ""
"Tento combobox má niekoľko užitočných vlastností, ktoré môžeme využiť: "
"[editable](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formcomboboxdelegate.html#editable-prop), [displayText](https://api.kde.org/"
"qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formcomboboxdelegate.html#displayText-"
"prop) a [displayMode](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-"
"formcard-formcomboboxdelegate.html#displayMode-prop)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:343
msgid ""
"Setting `editable: true` allows the user to edit the text of the combobox, "
"which is useful in case adding new combobox options is needed:"
msgstr ""
"Nastavenie `editable: true` umožňuje používateľovi upravovať text comboboxu, "
"čo je užitočné v prípade, keď je potrebné pridať nové možnosti do comboboxu:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:347
msgid ""
"Whenever you need to show additional text before each option, you can use "
"something like `displayText: \"Profile: \" + currentText`:"
msgstr ""
"Kedykoľvek potrebujete zobraziť dodatočný text pred každou možnosťou, môžete "
"použiť niečo ako `displayText: \"Profile: \" + currentText`:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:351
msgid ""
"And the most interesting one, which we will be using in our example, is "
"[displayMode](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formcomboboxdelegate.html#displayMode-prop). It can have three options:"
msgstr ""
"A najzaujímavejšia, ktorú budeme používať v našom príklade, je [displayMode]"
"(https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formcomboboxdelegate.html#displayMode-prop). Má tri možnosti:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:353
msgid ""
"**FormComboBoxDelegate.ComboBox**: the standard small box showing a list of "
"options."
msgstr ""
"**FormComboBoxDelegate.ComboBox**: štandardné malé pole zobrazujúce zoznam "
"možností."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:357
msgid ""
"**FormComboBoxDelegate.Dialog**: a dialog showing a list of options in the "
"middle of the window, like a [Kirigami.OverlaySheet](docs:kirigami;org.kde."
"kirigami.OverlaySheet)."
msgstr ""
"**FormComboBoxDelegate.Dialog**: dialóg zobrazujúci zoznam možností v strede "
"okna, podobne ako [Kirigami.OverlaySheet](docs:kirigami;org.kde.kirigami."
"OverlaySheet)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:361
msgid ""
"**FormComboBoxDelegate.Page**: a new page containing a list of options shown "
"in a separate window."
msgstr ""
"**FormComboBoxDelegate.Page**: nová stránka obsahujúca zoznam možností "
"zobrazená v samostatnom okne."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:365
msgid ""
"Add the following between the \"Current Color Scheme\" and \"Show Tray Icon"
"\" delegates in your \"General\" form card."
msgstr ""
"Pridajte nasledovné medzi delegáty \"Current Color Scheme\" a \"Show Tray "
"Icon\" vo vašej formulárovej karte \"General\"."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:378
msgid "With the checkbox, our Settings page should look like this:"
msgstr "S checkboxom by naša stránka Nastavení mala vyzerať takto:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:382
msgid "FormDelegateSeparator"
msgstr "FormDelegateSeparator"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:384
msgid ""
"Our Settings page is taking shape, but each section is starting to get long. "
"We can add a few [FormDelegateSeparator](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-"
"kirigamiaddons-formcard-formdelegateseparator.html) instances to make our "
"page tidier:"
msgstr ""
"Naša stránka Nastavení nadobúda tvar, ale každá sekcia začína byť dlhá. "
"Môžeme pridať niekoľko inštancií [FormDelegateSeparator](https://api.kde.org/"
"qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formdelegateseparator.html), aby bola "
"naša stránka prehľadnejšia:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:388
msgid ""
"Generally, you may use separators whenever you see major distinctions "
"between components, although the choice of where to place them is ultimately "
"yours. For example, in the General section, the checkbox differs from its "
"previous components as it doesn't start with text; in the Autosave section, "
"the separator groups the radio buttons together; and in the Accounts "
"section, adding a separator between the last account and the button provides "
"some additional focus to the button."
msgstr ""
"Vo všeobecnosti môžete použiť oddeľovače vždy, keď vidíte hlavné rozdiely "
"medzi komponentmi, hoci voľba, kam ich umiestniť, je nakoniec na vás. "
"Napríklad v sekcii Všeobecné sa zaškrtávacie políčko líši od "
"predchádzajúcich komponentov tým, že nezačína textom; v sekcii Automatické "
"ukladanie oddeľovač zoskupuje prepínacie tlačidlá; a v sekcii Účty pridanie "
"oddeľovača medzi posledný účet a tlačidlo poskytuje tlačidlu dodatočný dôraz."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:390
msgid ""
"The [above](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formdelegateseparator.html#above-prop) and [below](https://api.kde.org/qml-"
"org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formdelegateseparator.html#below-prop) "
"properties are rather self-explanatory when it comes to their use: you pass "
"the `id` of the components above and below the separator. When they are set, "
"the separator will swiftly disappear whenever the above or below item is "
"highlighted/hovered. They are most useful, for instance, when you need to "
"generate components dynamically and you can't automatically assume which "
"item will come immediately before or after the separator. That would be the "
"case in the Accounts section of our application once the logic to add new "
"accounts were actually implemented, in which case we could always grab the "
"last item in the model to do so."
msgstr ""
"Vlastnosti [above](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-"
"formdelegateseparator.html#above-prop) a [below](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-"
"kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formdelegateseparator.html#below-prop) sú celkom "
"samovysvetľujúce, pokiaľ ide o ich použitie: odovzdáte `id` komponentov nad "
"a pod oddeľovačom. Keď sú nastavené, oddeľovač rýchlo zmizne vždy, keď je "
"položka nad alebo pod ním zvýraznená/podržaná myšou. Sú najužitočnejšie "
"napríklad pri použití [FormDelegateSeparator](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-"
"kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formdelegateseparator.html) v situácii, kde môže "
"skončiť vedľa iných oddeľovačov alebo hlavičiek sekcií."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-delegates/index.md:394
msgid ""
"Notice how the separator above the tray icon setting does not appear while "
"it is hovered."
msgstr ""
"Všimnite si, ako sa oddeľovač nad nastavením ikony v lište nezobrazí, keď je "
"na ňom kurzor."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:0
msgid "Introduction to Kirigami Addons"
msgstr "Úvod do Kirigami Addons"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:0
msgid "Get acquainted with Kirigami Addons components"
msgstr "Oboznámte sa s komponentmi Kirigami Addons"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:10
msgid ""
"Here you will be setting up your new Kirigami Addons project and be "
"introduced to a few useful components."
msgstr ""
"Tu nastavíte váš nový projekt Kirigami Addons a budete oboznámení s "
"niekoľkými užitočnými komponentmi."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:12
msgid ""
"These components make use of KDE's localization facilities, so before we "
"start using these, we will need to set a little project that makes use of "
"[KLocalizedContext](docs:ki18n;KLocalizedContext)."
msgstr ""
"Tieto komponenty využívajú lokalizačné nástroje KDE, takže predtým, než ich "
"začneme používať, budeme musieť nastaviť malý projekt, ktorý využíva "
"[KLocalizedContext](docs:ki18n;KLocalizedContext)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:14
msgid "Setting up your project"
msgstr "Nastavenie vášho projektu"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:16
msgid "The initial project structure will look like so:"
msgstr "Počiatočná štruktúra projektu bude vyzerať takto:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:25
#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/introduction-actions/index.md:145
#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/setup-cpp/index.md:101
#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/setup-python/index.md:44
msgid "Tip"
msgstr "Hore"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:27
#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/setup-cpp/index.md:103
msgid "You can quickly create this file structure with:"
msgstr "Túto štruktúru súborov môžete rýchlo vytvoriť pomocou:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:37
msgid "We start by using a very standard `CMakeLists.txt`:"
msgstr "Začneme použitím veľmi štandardného `CMakeLists.txt`:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:41
msgid "The interesting part will be the `main.cpp`:"
msgstr "Zaujímavá časť bude `main.cpp`:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:45
msgid ""
"If you have read our [KXmlGui tutorial](/docs/getting-started/kxmlgui) or "
"the last Kirigami tutorial on the [Kirigami About page](/docs/getting-"
"started/kirigami/advanced-add_about_page), much of this will seem familiar "
"to you."
msgstr ""
"Ak ste si prečítali náš [tutoriál KXmlGui](/docs/getting-started/kxmlgui) "
"alebo posledný tutoriál Kirigami o [stránke O programe Kirigami](/docs/"
"getting-started/kirigami/advanced-add_about_page), veľa z toho sa vám bude "
"zdať známe."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:47
msgid ""
"We create our application and use [KAboutData](docs:kcoreaddons;"
"KAboutData)'s default constructor to add the metadata of our application, "
"add ourselves as an author, and then use [setApplicationData()](docs:"
"kcoreaddons;KAboutData::setApplicationData) to finish the process. For "
"later, we also set an application icon that comes from the system theme."
msgstr ""
"Vytvoríme našu aplikáciu a použijeme predvolený konštruktor [KAboutData]"
"(docs:kcoreaddons;KAboutData) na pridanie metadát našej aplikácie, pridáme "
"sa ako autor a potom použijeme [setApplicationData()](docs:kcoreaddons;"
"KAboutData::setApplicationData) na dokončenie procesu. Pre neskoršie "
"použitie tiež nastavíme ikonu aplikácie, ktorá pochádza zo systémovej témy."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:49
msgid ""
"We then use a lambda in [qmlRegisterSingletonType()](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/"
"qqml-h.html#qmlRegisterSingletonType) to directly send the metadata of our "
"application to the QML side, exposing its properties."
msgstr ""
"Potom použijeme lambda výraz v [qmlRegisterSingletonType()](https://doc.qt."
"io/qt-6/qqml-h.html#qmlRegisterSingletonType) na priame odoslanie metadát "
"našej aplikácie na stranu QML, čím sprístupníme jej vlastnosti."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:51
msgid ""
"We then instantiate our QML engine, and set its [context](docs:qtqml;"
"QQmlContext) to use KDE's [KLocalizedContext](docs:ki18n;KLocalizedContext), "
"used to integrate translated strings, passing the just created engine as a "
"parameter."
msgstr ""
"Potom vytvoríme inštanciu nášho QML enginu a nastavíme jeho [kontext](docs:"
"qtqml;QQmlContext) na používanie [KLocalizedContext](docs:ki18n;"
"KLocalizedContext) od KDE, ktorý slúži na integráciu preložených reťazcov, "
"pričom ako parameter odovzdáme práve vytvorený engine."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:53
msgid ""
"We simply load our QML file from the resource file, and now we just need to "
"take care of our initial QML file."
msgstr ""
"Jednoducho načítame náš súbor QML zo súboru zdrojov a teraz sa stačí "
"postarať o náš počiatočný súbor QML."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:55
msgid "FormCard and FormButtonDelegate"
msgstr "FormCard a FormButtonDelegate"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:57
msgid ""
"The idea for our app is to design our own Kirigami Addons gallery, "
"showcasing multiple components, one per page. The main page will contain a "
"simple list of buttons in a [ColumnLayout](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qml-"
"qtquick-layouts-columnlayout.html), each opening a separate page."
msgstr ""
"Nápad pre našu aplikáciu je navrhnúť vlastnú galériu Kirigami Addons, ktorá "
"ukáže viaceré komponenty, jeden na stránku. Hlavná stránka bude obsahovať "
"jednoduchý zoznam tlačidiel v [ColumnLayout](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qml-"
"qtquick-layouts-columnlayout.html), pričom každé otvorí samostatnú stránku."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:59
msgid "Initially, our `Main.qml` should look like this:"
msgstr "Náš `Main.qml` by mal pôvodne vyzerať takto:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:63
msgid ""
"We use our handy [pageStack](/docs/getting-started/kirigami/components-"
"pagerow_pagestack) to set the initial page to a [Kirigami.ScrollablePage]"
"(https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigami-scrollablepage.html)."
msgstr ""
"Používame náš praktický [pageStack](/docs/getting-started/kirigami/"
"components-pagerow_pagestack) na nastavenie úvodnej stránky na [Kirigami."
"ScrollablePage](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigami-scrollablepage."
"html)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:65
msgid ""
"While we could use a [FormLayout](/docs/getting-started/kirigami/components-"
"formlayouts) together with [QtQuick Controls components](components-"
"controls) to achieve our goal, here you will be introduced to [FormCard]"
"(https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formcard.html)."
msgstr ""
"Hoci by sme mohli použiť [FormLayout](/docs/getting-started/kirigami/"
"components-formlayouts) spolu s [komponentmi QtQuick Controls](components-"
"controls) na dosiahnutie nášho cieľa, tu vám predstavíme [FormCard](https://"
"api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-kirigamiaddons-formcard-formcard.html)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:67
msgid ""
"The main purpose of a FormCard is to serve as a container for other "
"components while following a color different from the background, in a "
"similar manner to a [Kirigami.Card](docs:kirigami;org.kde.kirigami.Card), "
"but for settings windows. You can have multiple FormCards in your "
"application to indicate different sections. Your FormCard is also expected "
"to be a direct child of a [ColumnLayout](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qml-qtquick-"
"layouts-columnlayout.html)."
msgstr ""
"Hlavným účelom FormCard je slúžiť ako kontajner pre iné komponenty s farbou "
"odlišnou od pozadia, podobným spôsobom ako [Kirigami.Card](docs:kirigami;org."
"kde.kirigami.Card), ale pre okná nastavení. V aplikácii môžete mať viacero "
"FormCard na označenie rôznych sekcií. Váš FormCard by mal byť tiež priamym "
"potomkom [ColumnLayout](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qml-qtquick-layouts-"
"columnlayout.html)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:69
msgid ""
"Importing `org.kde.kirigamiaddons.formcard` makes all FormCard components "
"available to your QML file."
msgstr ""
"Import `org.kde.kirigamiaddons.formcard` sprístupní všetky komponenty "
"FormCard vo vašom súbore QML."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:71
msgid ""
"We will have only a single section in our main page, so we add a single "
"FormCard:"
msgstr ""
"Na našej hlavnej stránke budeme mať iba jednu sekciu, takže pridáme jeden "
"FormCard:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:75
msgid ""
"The great thing about FormCard is that it does automatic layouting for you. "
"In other words, just the order of its components is enough to indicate their "
"position inside the FormCard, no [Layout attached properties](https://doc.qt."
"io/qt-6/qml-qtquick-layouts-layout.html) are necessary and you are expected "
"not to use [anchors](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qtquick-positioning-anchors."
"html) or [positioners](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qtquick-positioning-layouts."
"html)."
msgstr ""
"Skvelou vecou na FormCard je, že za vás vykonáva automatické rozloženie. "
"Inými slovami, stačí poradie jeho komponentov na určenie ich pozície vo "
"vnútri FormCard, žiadne [pripojené vlastnosti Layout](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/"
"qml-qtquick-layouts-layout.html) nie sú potrebné a neočakáva sa, že budete "
"používať [anchors](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qtquick-positioning-anchors.html) "
"alebo [positioners](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qtquick-positioning-layouts.html)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:77
msgid "We can simply add a few buttons inside our FormCard:"
msgstr "Do nášho FormCard môžeme jednoducho pridať niekoľko tlačidiel:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:81
msgid ""
"That's it! The buttons are not usable just yet, but we are now set up to "
"play with our About pages!"
msgstr ""
"To je všetko! Tlačidlá ešte nie sú použiteľné, ale teraz sme pripravení "
"experimentovať s našimi stránkami O aplikácii!"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:83
msgid "We then build and run it like so:"
msgstr "Potom to zostavíme a spustíme takto:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/addons-introduction/index.md:92
msgid ""
"To see other ways to build your application (for example, on Windows), see "
"the [Getting Started with Kirigami](/docs/getting-started/kirigami/"
"introduction-getting_started) page."
msgstr ""
"Ak chcete vidieť iné spôsoby zostavenia vašej aplikácie (napríklad na "
"Windows), pozrite si stránku [Začíname s Kirigami](/docs/getting-started/"
"kirigami/introduction-getting_started)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-add_about_page/index.md:0
msgid "About page"
msgstr "Stránka O aplikácii"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-add_about_page/index.md:0
msgid "Information about your application"
msgstr "Informácie o vašej aplikácii"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-add_about_page/index.md:10
msgid ""
"[Kirigami.AboutPage](docs:kirigami;org.kde.kirigami.AboutPage) allows you to "
"have a page that shows the copyright notice of the application together with "
"the list of contributors and some information of which platform it's running "
"on."
msgstr ""
"[Kirigami.AboutPage](docs:kirigami;org.kde.kirigami.AboutPage) vám umožňuje "
"mať stránku, ktorá zobrazuje oznámenie o autorských právach aplikácie spolu "
"so zoznamom prispievateľov a informáciami o tom, na akej platforme beží."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-add_about_page/index.md:12
msgid ""
"First, we are going to edit our `main.cpp` file from previous tutorials."
msgstr "Najskôr upravíme náš súbor `main.cpp` z predchádzajúcich tutoriálov."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-add_about_page/index.md:14
#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/setup-cpp/index.md:202
msgid "main.cpp"
msgstr "main.cpp"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-add_about_page/index.md:18
msgid ""
"In the `main.cpp` file we include [KAboutData](docs:kcoreaddons;KAboutData), "
"a core KDE frameworks component that lets us store information about our "
"application. This information can then be reused by many other KDE "
"Frameworks components. We instantiate a new `aboutData` object with its "
"fairly complete default constructor and add author information."
msgstr ""
"V súbore `main.cpp` zahrnieme [KAboutData](docs:kcoreaddons;KAboutData), "
"základný komponent KDE frameworkov, ktorý nám umožňuje ukladať informácie o "
"našej aplikácii. Tieto informácie potom môžu byť znovu použité mnohými "
"ďalšími komponentmi KDE Frameworks. Vytvoríme nový objekt `aboutData` s jeho "
"pomerne kompletným predvoleným konštruktorom a pridáme informácie o autorovi."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-add_about_page/index.md:20
msgid ""
"After all the required information has been set, we call [KAboutData::"
"setApplicationData()](docs:kcoreaddons;KAboutData::setApplicationData) to "
"initialize the properties of the [QApplication ](docs:qtwidgets;"
"QApplication) object."
msgstr ""
"Po nastavení všetkých požadovaných informácií zavoláme [KAboutData::"
"setApplicationData()](docs:kcoreaddons;KAboutData::setApplicationData) na "
"inicializáciu vlastností objektu [QApplication ](docs:qtwidgets;"
"QApplication)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-add_about_page/index.md:22
msgid ""
"We then create a [qmlRegisterSingletonType()](docs:qtqml;QQmlEngine::"
"qmlRegisterSingletonType). This is used to allow us to import the C++ code "
"as a module in our `main.qml` with `import org.kde.example 1.0`."
msgstr ""
"Potom vytvoríme [qmlRegisterSingletonType()](docs:qtqml;QQmlEngine::"
"qmlRegisterSingletonType). To sa používa na to, aby sme mohli importovať kód "
"C++ ako modul v našom `main.qml` pomocou `import org.kde.example 1.0`."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-add_about_page/index.md:24
msgid ""
"Its first argument is the URI that will be used for the import, the second "
"and third arguments are major and minor versions respectively, the fourth is "
"the type name, the name that we will call when accessing our `About` type, "
"and the last is a reference to the C++ object that is exposed to QML. In the "
"latter's case, we use a [lambda](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/"
"lambda) to instantiate the `aboutData` of our application in place."
msgstr ""
"Jeho prvý argument je URI, ktoré sa použije pre import, druhý a tretí "
"argument sú hlavná a vedľajšia verzia, štvrtý je názov typu, meno, ktoré "
"budeme volať pri prístupe k nášmu typu `About`, a posledný je odkaz na "
"objekt C++, ktorý je sprístupnený pre QML. V druhom prípade používame "
"[lambda výraz](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/lambda) na "
"vytvorenie inštancie `aboutData` našej aplikácie na mieste."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-add_about_page/index.md:26
msgid "main.qml"
msgstr "main.qml"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-add_about_page/index.md:30
msgid ""
"First, we use the import we defined in the `main.cpp` file, namely `org.kde."
"example`. We then add a [Kirigami.Action](docs:kirigami;org.kde.kirigami."
"Action) to our [global drawer](docs:kirigami;org.kde.kirigami.GlobalDrawer) "
"that will send us to the About page, and create a component with a [Kirigami."
"AboutPage](docs:kirigami;org.kde.kirigami.AboutPage) in it, which expects a "
"[KAboutData::applicationData()](docs:kcoreaddons;KAboutData::"
"applicationData) object. We exposed precisely that in our `main.cpp` and "
"called it `About`, so we can pass it here."
msgstr ""
"Najprv použijeme import, ktorý sme definovali v súbore `main.cpp`, a to `org."
"kde.example`. Potom pridáme [Kirigami.Action](docs:kirigami;org.kde.kirigami."
"Action) do nášho [globálneho vysúvacieho panela](docs:kirigami;org.kde."
"kirigami.GlobalDrawer), ktorá nás pošle na stránku O programe, a vytvoríme "
"komponent s [Kirigami.AboutPage](docs:kirigami;org.kde.kirigami.AboutPage), "
"ktorý očakáva objekt [KAboutData::applicationData()](docs:kcoreaddons;"
"KAboutData::applicationData). Presne to sme sprístupnili v našom súbore "
"`main.cpp`."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-add_about_page/index.md:33
msgid "CMakeLists"
msgstr "CMakeLists"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-add_about_page/index.md:37
msgid ""
"In the `CMakeLists.txt` file in our top-level folder, be sure to have "
"`CoreAddons` in your [find_package()](https://cmake.org/cmake/help/latest/"
"command/find_package.html) call. It is needed for [KAboutData](docs:"
"kcoreaddons;KAboutData)."
msgstr ""
"V súbore `CMakeLists.txt` v našom koreňovom priečinku sa uistite, že máte "
"`CoreAddons` vo vašom volaní [find_package()](https://cmake.org/cmake/help/"
"latest/command/find_package.html). Je potrebný pre [KAboutData](docs:"
"kcoreaddons;KAboutData)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-add_about_page/index.md:41
msgid ""
"In the `CMakeLists.txt` file in the `src/` directory, nothing is needed "
"since we instantiated out `aboutData` in place."
msgstr ""
"V súbore `CMakeLists.txt` v adresári `src/` nie je nič potrebné, pretože sme "
"inštanciovali náš `aboutData` na mieste."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-add_about_page/index.md:44
#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/setup-cpp/index.md:330
#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/setup-python/index.md:145
msgid "Running the application"
msgstr "Spustenie aplikácie"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-add_about_page/index.md:46
msgid ""
"Now if you run your application and trigger the \"About\" action in the "
"global drawer you should see our about page."
msgstr ""
"Ak teraz spustíte vašu aplikáciu a aktivujete akciu \"O aplikácii\" v "
"globálnej zásuvke, mali by ste vidieť našu stránku O aplikácii."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-add_about_page/index.md:48
msgid "![Screenshot of the Kirigami About Page](about-page.png)"
msgstr "![Screenshot of the Kirigami About Page](about-page.png)"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:0
msgid "Connect logic to your QML user interface"
msgstr "Prepojte logiku s vaším používateľským rozhraním QML"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:0
msgid ""
"Connect a backend to do calculations and supply your user interface with "
"data to display"
msgstr ""
"Prepojte backend na vykonávanie výpočtov a zásobovanie vášho používateľského "
"rozhrania dátami na zobrazenie"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:10
msgid ""
"To integrate logic into the application, we need C++ backend classes that "
"can do the important calculations. Writing logic in the QML files is "
"discouraged, so try to move as much as possible to the backend such that QML "
"is used only for displaying the user interface."
msgstr ""
"Na integráciu logiky do aplikácie potrebujeme backendové triedy C++, ktoré "
"dokážu vykonávať dôležité výpočty. Písanie logiky v súboroch QML sa "
"neodporúča, preto sa pokúste presunúť čo najviac do backendu, aby sa QML "
"používal iba na zobrazovanie používateľského rozhrania."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:12
msgid ""
"We will use the [Using separate files in a C++ project](/docs/getting-"
"started/kirigami/introduction-separatefiles) tutorial code as our base."
msgstr ""
"Ako základ použijeme kód z tutoriálu [Používanie samostatných súborov v "
"projekte C++](/docs/getting-started/kirigami/introduction-separatefiles)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:14
#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:24
#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/setup-cpp/index.md:83
#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/setup-python/index.md:23
#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/setup-rust/index.md:22
msgid "Project structure"
msgstr "Štruktúra projektu"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:33
msgid "Changes to existing code"
msgstr "Zmeny existujúceho kódu"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:35
#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:87
msgid "src/components/backend.h"
msgstr "CMakeLists"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:37
msgid ""
"First, create the header file that will have code exposed to QML, namely the "
"`Backend` type:"
msgstr ""
"Najskôr vytvorte hlavičkový súbor, ktorý bude mať kód vystavený do QML, "
"konkrétne typ `Backend`:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:41
msgid ""
"There are two things needed to expose C++ code to QML, and one of them is "
"simply using the [QML_ELEMENT](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qqmlintegration-h."
"html#QML_ELEMENT) macro, available in the `<QtQml/qqmlregistration.h>` "
"header."
msgstr ""
"Na sprístupnenie kódu C++ pre QML sú potrebné dve veci a jednou z nich je "
"jednoduché použitie makra [QML_ELEMENT](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/"
"qqmlintegration-h.html#QML_ELEMENT), dostupného v hlavičkovom súbore `<QtQml/"
"qqmlregistration.h>`."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:43
msgid ""
"The backend will be created as a singleton, which means it will only be "
"created once and exist for the whole duration of the application lifetime. "
"For this, we use the [QML_SINGLETON](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qqmlintegration-"
"h.html#QML_SINGLETON) macro."
msgstr ""
"Backend bude vytvorený ako singleton, čo znamená, že bude vytvorený iba raz "
"a bude existovať po celú dobu životnosti aplikácie. Na to používame makro "
"[QML_SINGLETON](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qqmlintegration-h.html#QML_SINGLETON)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:45
#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:123
msgid "src/components/backend.cpp"
msgstr "CMakeLists"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:47
msgid "We can add our initial code for the constructor to `backend.cpp`:"
msgstr "Do `backend.cpp` môžeme pridať náš počiatočný kód pre konštruktor:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:51
#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:131
msgid "src/components/ExposePage.qml"
msgstr "CMakeLists"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:53
msgid ""
"From now on, the backend will be known to QML as the `Backend` QML type. It "
"is contained in a module called `org.kde.tutorial.components`."
msgstr ""
"Odteraz bude backend známy pre QML ako typ QML `Backend`. Je obsiahnutý v "
"module s názvom `org.kde.tutorial.components`."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:55
msgid ""
"This means that just by adding the import in a QML file, it is possible to "
"use the code exposed from C++:"
msgstr ""
"To znamená, že len pridaním importu v súbore QML je možné použiť kód "
"vystavený z C++:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:61
msgid ""
"To start from a clean slate using the existent application code, create a "
"new QML component that contains an empty page:"
msgstr ""
"Na začatie od nuly s použitím existujúceho kódu aplikácie vytvorte nový "
"komponent QML, ktorý obsahuje prázdnu stránku:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:65
msgid "src/Main.qml"
msgstr "src/Main.qml"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:67
msgid ""
"To actually show the new page, let's create a menu option that [pushes the "
"new page](/docs/getting-started/kirigami/components-pagerow_pagestack/) to "
"the application, just so we can test the model more easily."
msgstr ""
"Na skutočné zobrazenie novej stránky vytvorme položku menu, ktorá [pridá "
"novú stránku](/docs/getting-started/kirigami/components-pagerow_pagestack/) "
"do aplikácie, aby sme mohli jednoduchšie otestovať model."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:69
msgid ""
"For this, we can use a new [Kirigami.Action](/docs/getting-started/kirigami/"
"components-actions/) together with [Qt.createComponent()](https://doc.qt.io/"
"qt-6/qtqml-javascript-dynamicobjectcreation.html) to generate the page on "
"the fly:"
msgstr ""
"Na to môžeme použiť novú [Kirigami.Action](/docs/getting-started/kirigami/"
"components-actions/) spolu s [Qt.createComponent()](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/"
"qtqml-javascript-dynamicobjectcreation.html) na generovanie stránky za behu:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:73
#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-understanding_cmakelists/index.md:96
msgid "src/components/CMakeLists.txt"
msgstr "CMakeLists"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:75
msgid ""
"Lastly, add the newly created `backend.h`, `backend.cpp` and `ExposePage."
"qml` to CMake:"
msgstr ""
"Nakoniec pridajte novo vytvorené `backend.h`, `backend.cpp` a `ExposePage."
"qml` do CMake:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:79
msgid ""
"Adding the files to an existing QML module in CMake is the second part to "
"exposing code to QML."
msgstr ""
"Pridanie súborov do existujúceho modulu QML v CMake je druhá časť "
"vystavovania kódu do QML."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:81
msgid ""
"Note that the QML module should have been created with either "
"[ecm_add_qml_module()](https://api.kde.org/ecm/module/ECMQmlModule.html) or "
"[qt_add_qml_module()](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qt-add-qml-module.html), as "
"they are required for [declarative registration](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/"
"qtqml-cppintegration-definetypes.html)."
msgstr ""
"Upozorňujeme, že modul QML by mal byť vytvorený buď pomocou "
"[ecm_add_qml_module()](https://api.kde.org/ecm/module/ECMQmlModule.html) "
"alebo [qt_add_qml_module()](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qt-add-qml-module.html), "
"pretože sú vyžadované pre [deklaratívnu registráciu](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/"
"qtqml-cppintegration-definetypes.html)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:83
msgid ""
"Now you should be able to compile and install the project with [the same "
"steps as before](/docs/getting-started/kirigami/setup-cpp/#running-the-"
"application)."
msgstr ""
"Teraz by ste mali byť schopní skompilovať a nainštalovať projekt [rovnakými "
"krokmi ako predtým](/docs/getting-started/kirigami/setup-cpp/#running-the-"
"application)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:85
msgid "Making it functional"
msgstr "Urobenie funkčným"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:89
msgid ""
"Now we have connected the class holding the future logic to the application, "
"but it still doesn't do anything. To change that, let's add a property to "
"the class. Properties are a lot more than a simple variable. They can inform "
"the UI about changes so it can update the right areas."
msgstr ""
"Teraz sme pripojili triedu obsahujúcu budúcu logiku k aplikácii, ale stále "
"nič nerobí. Aby sme to zmenili, pridajme do triedy vlastnosť. Vlastnosti sú "
"oveľa viac než jednoduchá premenná. Môžu informovať UI o zmenách, aby mohlo "
"aktualizovať správne oblasti."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:91
msgid ""
"Right under the `QML_SINGLETON` macro, add a new [Q_PROPERTY](docs:qtcore;"
"QObject::Q_PROPERTY)."
msgstr ""
"Priamo pod makrom `QML_SINGLETON` pridajte novú [Q_PROPERTY](docs:qtcore;"
"QObject::Q_PROPERTY)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:97
msgid ""
"This may seem like a lot of code to just read and write some code from the "
"backend. However, a closer look reveals that reading the property from the "
"UI can already run some logic—same when it is written to. In this case, it "
"will automatically inform the frontend and backend of changes."
msgstr ""
"Toto sa môže zdať ako veľa kódu len na čítanie a zápis z backendu. Avšak "
"bližší pohľad odhalí, že čítanie vlastnosti z UI už môže spúšťať nejakú "
"logiku—rovnako keď sa do nej zapisuje. V tomto prípade automaticky informuje "
"frontend aj backend o zmenách."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:99
msgid ""
"The reading and writing is based on the concept of [getter and setter "
"functions](https://www.w3schools.com/cpp/cpp_encapsulation.asp). Go ahead "
"and add a new private attribute to your class that holds the data, as well "
"as the relevant getter and setter functions."
msgstr ""
"Čítanie a zápis je založený na koncepte [funkcií getter a setter](https://"
"www.w3schools.com/cpp/cpp_encapsulation.asp). Pokračujte a pridajte do vašej "
"triedy nový privátny atribút, ktorý drží dáta, ako aj príslušné funkcie "
"getter a setter."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:101
msgid "Add a new private section with the following:"
msgstr "Pridajte novú privátnu sekciu s nasledovným:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:108
msgid "And add the following to the existing public section:"
msgstr "A pridajte nasledovné do existujúcej verejnej sekcie:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:117
msgid ""
"The first function is the getter, the second the setter, and the third a "
"signal that is emitted when the property is changed. They match the READ, "
"WRITE and NOTIFY parts of the above `Q_PROPERTY`."
msgstr ""
"Prvá funkcia je getter, druhá setter a tretia je signál, ktorý je emitovaný "
"pri zmene vlastnosti. Zodpovedajú častiam READ, WRITE a NOTIFY vyššie "
"uvedeného `Q_PROPERTY`."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:119
msgid "The result should look like the following:"
msgstr "Výsledok by mal vyzerať nasledovne:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:125
msgid ""
"The signal doesn't need any implementation in the `backend.cpp` file, since "
"it doesn't do much more than being emitted, but the getter and setter need "
"to be implemented similar to the following:"
msgstr ""
"Signál nepotrebuje žiadnu implementáciu v súbore `backend.cpp`, pretože "
"nerobí oveľa viac než to, že je emitovaný, ale getter a setter musia byť "
"implementované podobne ako nasledovné:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:129
msgid ""
"As you can see, when the setter is called, the signal will be emitted, and "
"inform the ui and backend of the change."
msgstr ""
"Ako vidíte, keď sa zavolá setter, signál bude emitovaný a informuje UI a "
"backend o zmene."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_backend/index.md:133
msgid ""
"To display the text, add a [Kirigami.Heading](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-"
"kde-kirigami-heading.html) to `src/components/ExposePage.qml` under the "
"[title](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qml-qtquick-controls-page.html#title-prop) "
"property of the [Kirigami.Page](docs:kirigami;org.kde.kirigami.Page) "
"component we added to the code."
msgstr ""
"Na zobrazenie textu pridajte [Kirigami.Heading](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-"
"kde-kirigami-heading.html) do `src/components/ExposePage.qml` pod vlastnosť "
"[title](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qml-qtquick-controls-page.html#title-prop) "
"komponentu [Kirigami.Page](docs:kirigami;org.kde.kirigami.Page), ktorý sme "
"pridali do kódu."

