msgid "Note"
msgstr "Poznámka"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:116
msgid ""
"The custom role names created by `roleNames()` are only usable when a model "
"is being delegated, and are not usable outside of it. See [Models and Views]"
"(docs:qtquick;qtquick-modelviewsdata-modelview.html#models)."
msgstr ""
"Vlastné názvy rolí vytvorené funkciou `roleNames()` sú použiteľné iba keď je "
"model delegovaný a nie sú použiteľné mimo neho. Pozrite si [Modely a "
"zobrazenia](docs:qtquick;qtquick-modelviewsdata-modelview.html#models)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:124
msgid ""
"Technically, models in Qt are represented as tables, with rows and columns. "
"So, what overriding `rowCount()` does is tell Qt how many rows are in a "
"model. Since we are just dealing with a one-dimensional array in this "
"tutorial, you can just think of \"rows\" as \"number of elements.\""
msgstr ""
"Technicky sú modely v Qt reprezentované ako tabuľky s riadkami a stĺpcami. "
"Takže prepísanie `rowCount()` povie Qt, koľko riadkov je v modeli. Keďže v "
"tomto tutoriáli pracujeme iba s jednorozmerným poľom, môžete si \"riadky\" "
"jednoducho predstaviť ako \"počet prvkov.\""

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:131
msgid "Overriding and Implementing `rowCount()`"
msgstr "Prekonanie a implementácia `rowCount()`"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:133
msgid ""
"Let's override the function in the `src/components/model.h` header file. The "
"[rowCount()](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qabstractitemmodel.html#rowCount) "
"function comes with its own parameter, but it will not be used in this "
"example and so doesn't need to be named."
msgstr ""
"Prepíšme funkciu v hlavičkovom súbore `src/components/model.h`. Funkcia "
"[rowCount()](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qabstractitemmodel.html#rowCount) "
"prichádza s vlastným parametrom, ale v tomto príklade sa nepoužije, a preto "
"ho netreba pomenovať."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:138
msgid ""
"Then, let's declare how many rows are in this model in `src/components/model."
"cpp`:"
msgstr ""
"Potom deklarujme, koľko riadkov je v tomto modeli v `src/components/model."
"cpp`:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:142
msgid "Overriding and Implementing `roleNames()`"
msgstr "Prekonanie a implementácia `roleNames()`"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:144
msgid ""
"Before we override `roleNames()`, we need to declare what the roles are in "
"the C++ side using a public enum. The reason for this is because these enum "
"values are passed into `data()` every time QML accesses a corresponding "
"role, and as such we can make `data()` return what we want."
msgstr ""
"Predtým, než prepíšeme `roleNames()`, musíme deklarovať, aké sú roly na "
"strane C++ pomocou verejného enumu. Dôvodom je to, že tieto hodnoty enumu sa "
"odovzdávajú do `data()` zakaždým, keď QML pristupuje k zodpovedajúcej role, "
"a ako také môžeme prinútiť `data()` vrátiť to, čo chceme."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:150
msgid ""
"Let's begin with creating the enum for roles in `src/components/model.h`, "
"where each value is a role for the C++ side."
msgstr ""
"Začnime vytvorením enum pre roly v `src/components/model.h`, kde každá "
"hodnota je rola pre stranu C++."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:155
msgid ""
"Once we have that settled, we can finally create what these roles are in the "
"QML side using a [QHash](docs:qtcore;qhash.html) where the keys are the "
"enumerated values paired with [QByteArrays](docs:qtcore;qbytearray.html). "
"This should go to `src/components/model.cpp`. The text in the QByteArray is "
"what's used in the actual QML code."
msgstr ""
"Keď to máme vyriešené, môžeme konečne vytvoriť tieto roly na strane QML "
"pomocou [QHash](docs:qtcore;qhash.html), kde kľúče sú enumerované hodnoty "
"spárované s [QByteArrays](docs:qtcore;qbytearray.html). Toto by malo ísť do "
"`src/components/model.cpp`. Text v QByteArray je to, čo sa používa v "
"skutočnom kóde QML."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:162
msgid ""
"In our example model, the role \"species\" can be used to retrieve the "
"QString key \"Feline\", \"Fox\", \"Goat\", each in a separate delegate. The "
"same can be done with the QStringList values for the character names list."
msgstr ""
"V našom vzorovom modeli možno rolu \"species\" použiť na získanie kľúča "
"QString \"Feline\", \"Fox\", \"Goat\", každý v samostatnom delegátovi. To "
"isté možno urobiť s hodnotami QStringList pre zoznam mien postáv."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:167
msgid "Overriding and Implementing `data()`"
msgstr "Prekonanie a implementácia `data()`"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:169
msgid ""
"There are two parameters that are passed to `data()`: `index` and `role`. "
"The `index` is the position of the data in the model. As previously stated, "
"`role` is used by QML to get specific data returned when it's accessing a "
"role."
msgstr ""
"Do funkcie `data()` sa odovzdávajú dva parametre: `index` a `role`. `index` "
"je pozícia dát v modeli. Ako bolo uvedené predtým, `role` sa používa v QML "
"na získanie konkrétnych dát vrátených pri prístupe k role."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:174
msgid ""
"In `data()`, we can use a switch statement to return the appropriate data "
"and data type depending on the role, which is possible as `data()` returns a "
"[QVariant](docs:qtcore;qvariant.html). We still need to make sure we get the "
"appropriate location of the data, though. In this example below, you can see "
"that a new iterator variable is being declared, which is set from the "
"beginning of the list plus the row of the index, and the data that the "
"iterator is pointing to is what is being returned."
msgstr ""
"Vo funkcii `data()` môžeme použiť príkaz switch na vrátenie príslušných dát "
"a dátového typu v závislosti od roly, čo je možné, pretože `data()` vracia "
"[QVariant](docs:qtcore;qvariant.html). Stále však musíme zabezpečiť, aby sme "
"získali správne umiestnenie dát. V nasledujúcom príklade vidíte, že sa "
"deklaruje nová premenná iterátora, ktorá je nastavená od začiatku zoznamu "
"plus riadok indexu, a dáta, na ktoré iterátor ukazuje, sú to, čo sa vracia."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:182
msgid ""
"We can't just return whatever data we want though. We may be trying to bind "
"data to a property with an incompatible data type, such as a QStringList to "
"a QString. You may have to do data conversion in order for the data to be "
"displayed properly. For this, we create a new private, static function named "
"`formatList()`."
msgstr ""
"Nemôžeme však vrátiť akékoľvek dáta, ktoré chceme. Môžeme sa pokúšať "
"naviazať dáta na vlastnosť s nekompatibilným dátovým typom, ako napríklad "
"QStringList na QString. Možno budete musieť vykonať konverziu dát, aby sa "
"dáta zobrazovali správne. Na to vytvoríme novú privátnu statickú funkciu s "
"názvom `formatList()`."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:187
msgid "This results in the following code in `src/components/model.cpp`:"
msgstr "Výsledkom je nasledovný kód v `src/components/model.cpp`:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:191
msgid "And the following code in `src/components/model.h`:"
msgstr "A nasledovný kód v `src/components/model.h`:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:195
msgid "Class Usage in QML"
msgstr "Použitie triedy v QML"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:197
msgid ""
"The QML file that is used will just contain three [Kirigami.AbstractCard]"
"(docs:kirigami;org.kde.kirigami.AbstractCard) components, where the key is "
"the header and the value is the content. These cards are created by "
"delegating an AbstractCard using a Repeater, where the custom model we "
"created acts as the model. The data is accessed using word `model`, followed "
"by the roles we declared in `roleNames()`."
msgstr ""
"Použitý súbor QML bude obsahovať iba tri komponenty [Kirigami.AbstractCard]"
"(docs:kirigami;org.kde.kirigami.AbstractCard), kde kľúč je hlavička a "
"hodnota je obsah. Tieto karty sa vytvárajú delegovaním AbstractCard pomocou "
"Repeatera, kde vlastný model, ktorý sme vytvorili, funguje ako model. K "
"dátam sa pristupuje pomocou slova `model`, za ktorým nasledujú roly, ktoré "
"sme deklarovali v `roleNames()`."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:206
msgid ""
"A screenshot of the C++ models in QML page showing a list of characters "
"organized per species"
msgstr ""
"Snímka obrazovky stránky C++ modelov v QML zobrazujúca zoznam postáv "
"organizovaných podľa druhov"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:208
msgid "Data Modification"
msgstr "Modifikácia dát"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:210
msgid "Editing Data Using `dataChanged()` and `setData()`"
msgstr "Úprava dát pomocou `dataChanged()` a `setData()`"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:212
msgid ""
"You may encounter a situation where you want to modify data in the model, "
"and have the changes reflected on the frontend side. Every time we change "
"data in the model, we must emit the `dataChanged()` signal which will apply "
"those changes on the frontend side at the specific cells specified in its "
"arguments. In this tutorial, we can just use the `index` argument of "
"[setData()](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qabstractitemmodel.html#setData)."
msgstr ""
"Môžete sa stretnúť so situáciou, keď chcete upraviť dáta v modeli a nechať "
"zmeny prejaviť na strane frontendu. Zakaždým, keď zmeníme dáta v modeli, "
"musíme emitovať signál `dataChanged()`, ktorý aplikuje tieto zmeny na strane "
"frontendu v konkrétnych bunkách uvedených v jeho argumentoch. V tomto "
"tutoriáli môžeme jednoducho použiť argument `index` funkcie [setData()]"
"(https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qabstractitemmodel.html#setData)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:218
msgid ""
"[setData()](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qabstractitemmodel.html#setData) is a "
"virtual function you can override so that modifying the data from the "
"frontend side automatically reflects those changes on the backend side. It "
"requires three parameters:"
msgstr ""
"[setData()](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qabstractitemmodel.html#setData) je "
"virtuálna funkcia, ktorú môžete prepísať tak, aby úprava dát zo strany "
"frontendu automaticky odrážala tieto zmeny na strane backendu. Vyžaduje tri "
"parametre:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:222
msgid "`index` - The location of the data."
msgstr "`index` - Umiestnenie dát."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:223
msgid "`value` - The contents of the new data."
msgstr "`value` - Obsah nových dát."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:224
msgid ""
"`role` - In this context, the role here is used to tell views how they "
"should handle data. The role here should be [Qt::EditRole](https://doc.qt.io/"
"qt-6/qt.html#ItemDataRole-enum)."
msgstr ""
"`role` - V tomto kontexte sa rola používa na informovanie zobrazení, ako "
"majú spracovať dáta. Rola by tu mala byť [Qt::EditRole](https://doc.qt.io/"
"qt-6/qt.html#ItemDataRole-enum)."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:227
msgid ""
"The `role` parameter in this case is used to ensure `setData()` can be "
"edited via user input (Qt::EditRole). Using `index`, we can use that to "
"determine the location of where the data should be edited with the contents "
"of `value`."
msgstr ""
"Parameter `role` sa v tomto prípade používa na zabezpečenie, že `setData()` "
"je možné upraviť prostredníctvom vstupu používateľa (Qt::EditRole). Pomocou "
"`index` môžeme určiť umiestnenie, kde majú byť dáta upravené s obsahom "
"`value`."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:236
msgid ""
"`setData()` does not automatically emit [dataChanged()](https://doc.qt.io/"
"qt-6/qabstractitemmodel.html#dataChanged) and that has to be done manually."
msgstr ""
"`setData()` automaticky neemituje [dataChanged()](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/"
"qabstractitemmodel.html#dataChanged) a to sa musí urobiť manuálne."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:241
msgid "With the corresponding addition in `src/components/model.h`:"
msgstr "S príslušným doplnením v `src/components/model.h`:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:245
msgid ""
"Let's update the QML code so that we can open up a prompt that allows us to "
"edit the model using a [Controls.Button](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qml-qtquick-"
"controls-button.html) attached to the cards."
msgstr ""
"Aktualizujme kód QML, aby sme mohli otvoriť dialóg, ktorý nám umožní upraviť "
"model pomocou [Controls.Button](https://doc.qt.io/qt-6/qml-qtquick-controls-"
"button.html) pripojeného ku kartám."

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:248
msgid ""
"Add the following [Kirigami.PromptDialog](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-"
"kirigami-dialogs-promptdialog.html) to the `src/components/ModelsPage.qml`, "
"together with a new edit button:"
msgstr ""
"Pridajte nasledujúci [Kirigami.PromptDialog](https://api.kde.org/qml-org-kde-"
"kirigami-dialogs-promptdialog.html) do `src/components/ModelsPage.qml` spolu "
"s novým tlačidlom na úpravu:"

#: content/docs/getting-started/kirigami/advanced-connect_models/index.md:252
msgid ""
"Now, whenever the values of the model change in the frontend, the changes "
"should automatically update on the backend."
msgstr ""
"Teraz, kedykoľvek sa zmenia hodnoty modelu na frontende, zmeny by sa mali "
"automaticky aktualizovať na backende."

